Planning tutorials.

For documentation, see the Cougaar training slides in this directory and:
  http://cougaar.org/projects/cougaar/

NOTE: THESE TUTORIALS WERE DESIGNED TO BE USED IN CONJUNCTION WITH THE COURSE SLIDES

RUNNING NOTE:  When running from XML, you cannot have a cougaar.rc on your config path.

---------------
Windows:
To build and run exercise 5:
  cd %COUGAAR_INSTALL_PATH%/tutorial/bin
  buildExercise.bat 5  (the class files are jarred under %COUGAAR_INSTALL_PATH%\lib)
  runExercise.bat 5
  
To build and run src (solutions) for exercise 5:
  cd %COUGAAR_INSTALL_PATH%/tutorial/bin
  buildSrc.bat 5   (the class files are jarred under %COUGAAR_INSTALL_PATH%\lib)
  runSrc.bat 5

For EXERCISES:
  code to work on is under %COUGAAR_INSTALL_PATH%\tutorial\exercises\org\cougaar\tutorial
  configs (some of which need to be modified) are under %COUGAAR_INSTALL_PATH%\tutorial\exercises\configs

For SOLUTIONS (Src):
  code is under %COUGAAR_INSTALL_PATH%\tutorial\src\org\cougaar\tutorial
  configs are under %COUGAAR_INSTALL_PATH%\tutorial\configs
  
  
---------------
Linux:
To run exercise 5:
  cd $CIP/tutorial/bin
  ./run.sh 5      # or any number 1 .. 11

Solution source is in:
  $CIP/tutorial/src/org/cougaar/tutorial

Exercise source is in:
  $CIP/tutorial/exercises/org/cougaar/tutorial
The above directory includes a build script:
  ./build.sh 5     # or any number 1 .. 11
and a run script:
  ./run.sh 5       # or any number 1 .. 11
